The paper presents a decentralized algorithm for solving the assignment problem, which involves matching agents to resources. This falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves game-theoretic concepts such as social welfare and competition, which are relevant to the category of game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm's convergence speed and scalability are also discussed, which are relevant to the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
